{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Think about your day for a second."},{"time":2000,"text":"You woke up, felt fresh air on your face as you walked out the door,"},{"time":5000,"text":"encountered new colleagues and had great discussions,"},{"time":7000,"text":"and felt in awe when you found something new."},{"time":9000,"text":"But I bet there's something you didn't think about today --"},{"time":11000,"text":"something so close to home"},{"time":13000,"text":"that you probably don't think about it very often at all."},{"time":15000,"text":"And that's that all the sensations, feelings,"},{"time":17000,"text":"decisions and actions"},{"time":19000,"text":"are mediated by the computer in your head"},{"time":21000,"text":"called the brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":23000,"text":"Now the brain may not look like much from the outside --"},{"time":25000,"text":"a couple pounds of pinkish-gray flesh,"},{"time":27000,"text":"amorphous --"},{"time":29000,"text":"but the last hundred years of neuroscience"},{"time":31000,"text":"have allowed us to zoom in on the brain,"},{"time":33000,"text":"and to see the intricacy of what lies within."},{"time":35000,"text":"And they've told us that this brain"},{"time":37000,"text":"is an incredibly complicated circuit"},{"time":39000,"text":"made out of hundreds of billions of cells called neurons."},{"time":43000,"text":"Now unlike a human-designed computer,"},{"time":46000,"text":"where there's a fairly small number of different parts --"},{"time":48000,"text":"we know how they work, because we humans designed them --"},{"time":51000,"text":"the brain is made out of thousands of different kinds of cells,"},{"time":54000,"text":"maybe tens of thousands."},{"time":56000,"text":"They come in different shapes; they're made out of different molecules."},{"time":58000,"text":"And they project and connect to different brain regions,"},{"time":61000,"text":"and they also change different ways in different disease states."}]},{"cues":[{"time":64000,"text":"Let's make it concrete."},{"time":66000,"text":"There's a class of cells,"},{"time":68000,"text":"a fairly small cell, an inhibitory cell, that quiets its neighbors."},{"time":71000,"text":"It's one of the cells that seems to be atrophied in disorders like schizophrenia."},{"time":75000,"text":"It's called the basket cell."},{"time":77000,"text":"And this cell is one of the thousands of kinds of cell"},{"time":79000,"text":"that we are learning about."},{"time":81000,"text":"New ones are being discovered everyday."},{"time":83000,"text":"As just a second example:"},{"time":85000,"text":"these pyramidal cells, large cells,"},{"time":87000,"text":"they can span a significant fraction of the brain."},{"time":89000,"text":"They're excitatory."},{"time":91000,"text":"And these are some of the cells"},{"time":93000,"text":"that might be overactive in disorders such as epilepsy."},{"time":96000,"text":"Every one of these cells"},{"time":98000,"text":"is an incredible electrical device."},{"time":101000,"text":"They receive input from thousands of upstream partners"},{"time":103000,"text":"and compute their own electrical outputs,"},{"time":106000,"text":"which then, if they pass a certain threshold,"},{"time":108000,"text":"will go to thousands of downstream partners."},{"time":110000,"text":"And this process, which takes just a millisecond or so,"},{"time":113000,"text":"happens thousands of times a minute"},{"time":115000,"text":"in every one of your 100 billion cells,"},{"time":117000,"text":"as long as you live"},{"time":119000,"text":"and think and feel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":122000,"text":"So how are we going to figure out what this circuit does?"},{"time":125000,"text":"Ideally, we could go through the circuit"},{"time":127000,"text":"and turn these different kinds of cell on and off"},{"time":130000,"text":"and see whether we could figure out"},{"time":132000,"text":"which ones contribute to certain functions"},{"time":134000,"text":"and which ones go wrong in certain pathologies."},{"time":136000,"text":"If we could activate cells, we could see what powers they can unleash,"},{"time":139000,"text":"what they can initiate and sustain."},{"time":141000,"text":"If we could turn them off,"},{"time":143000,"text":"then we could try and figure out what they're necessary for."},{"time":145000,"text":"And that's a story I'm going to tell you about today."},{"time":148000,"text":"And honestly, where we've gone through over the last 11 years,"},{"time":151000,"text":"through an attempt to find ways"},{"time":153000,"text":"of turning circuits and cells and parts and pathways of the brain"},{"time":155000,"text":"on and off,"},{"time":157000,"text":"both to understand the science"},{"time":159000,"text":"and also to confront some of the issues"},{"time":162000,"text":"that face us all as humans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":165000,"text":"Now before I tell you about the technology,"},{"time":168000,"text":"the bad news is that a significant fraction of us in this room,"},{"time":171000,"text":"if we live long enough,"},{"time":173000,"text":"will encounter, perhaps, a brain disorder."},{"time":175000,"text":"Already, a billion people"},{"time":177000,"text":"have had some kind of brain disorder"},{"time":179000,"text":"that incapacitates them,"},{"time":181000,"text":"and the numbers don't do it justice though."},{"time":183000,"text":"These disorders -- schizophrenia, Alzheimer's,"},{"time":185000,"text":"depression, addiction --"},{"time":187000,"text":"they not only steal our time to live, they change who we are."},{"time":190000,"text":"They take our identity and change our emotions"},{"time":192000,"text":"and change who we are as people."},{"time":195000,"text":"Now in the 20th century,"},{"time":198000,"text":"there was some hope that was generated"},{"time":201000,"text":"through the development of pharmaceuticals for treating brain disorders,"},{"time":204000,"text":"and while many drugs have been developed"},{"time":207000,"text":"that can alleviate symptoms of brain disorders,"},{"time":209000,"text":"practically none of them can be considered to be cured."},{"time":212000,"text":"And part of that's because we're bathing the brain in the chemical."},{"time":215000,"text":"This elaborate circuit"},{"time":217000,"text":"made out of thousands of different kinds of cell"},{"time":219000,"text":"is being bathed in a substance."},{"time":221000,"text":"That's also why, perhaps, most of the drugs, and not all, on the market"},{"time":223000,"text":"can present some kind of serious side effect too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":226000,"text":"Now some people have gotten some solace"},{"time":229000,"text":"from electrical stimulators that are implanted in the brain."},{"time":232000,"text":"And for Parkinson's disease,"},{"time":234000,"text":"Cochlear implants,"},{"time":236000,"text":"these have indeed been able"},{"time":238000,"text":"to bring some kind of remedy"},{"time":240000,"text":"to people with certain kinds of disorder."},{"time":242000,"text":"But electricity also will go in all directions --"},{"time":244000,"text":"the path of least resistance,"},{"time":246000,"text":"which is where that phrase, in part, comes from."},{"time":248000,"text":"And it also will affect normal circuits as well as the abnormal ones that you want to fix."},{"time":251000,"text":"So again, we're sent back to the idea"},{"time":253000,"text":"of ultra-precise control."},{"time":255000,"text":"Could we dial-in information precisely where we want it to go?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":259000,"text":"So when I started in neuroscience 11 years ago,"},{"time":263000,"text":"I had trained as an electrical engineer and a physicist,"},{"time":266000,"text":"and the first thing I thought about was,"},{"time":268000,"text":"if these neurons are electrical devices,"},{"time":270000,"text":"all we need to do is to find some way"},{"time":272000,"text":"of driving those electrical changes at a distance."},{"time":274000,"text":"If we could turn on the electricity in one cell,"},{"time":276000,"text":"but not its neighbors,"},{"time":278000,"text":"that would give us the tool we need to activate and shut down these different cells,"},{"time":281000,"text":"figure out what they do and how they contribute"},{"time":283000,"text":"to the networks in which they're embedded."},{"time":285000,"text":"And also it would allow us to have the ultra-precise control we need"},{"time":287000,"text":"in order to fix the circuit computations"},{"time":290000,"text":"that have gone awry."},{"time":292000,"text":"Now how are we going to do that?"},{"time":294000,"text":"Well there are many molecules that exist in nature,"},{"time":296000,"text":"which are able to convert light into electricity."},{"time":299000,"text":"You can think of them as little proteins"},{"time":301000,"text":"that are like solar cells."},{"time":303000,"text":"If we can install these molecules in neurons somehow,"},{"time":306000,"text":"then these neurons would become electrically drivable with light."},{"time":309000,"text":"And their neighbors, which don't have the molecule, would not."},{"time":312000,"text":"There's one other magic trick you need to make this all happen,"},{"time":314000,"text":"and that's the ability to get light into the brain."},{"time":317000,"text":"And to do that -- the brain doesn't feel pain -- you can put --"},{"time":320000,"text":"taking advantage of all the effort"},{"time":322000,"text":"that's gone into the Internet and communications and so on --"},{"time":324000,"text":"optical fibers connected to lasers"},{"time":326000,"text":"that you can use to activate, in animal models for example,"},{"time":328000,"text":"in pre-clinical studies,"},{"time":330000,"text":"these neurons and to see what they do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":332000,"text":"So how do we do this?"},{"time":334000,"text":"Around 2004,"},{"time":336000,"text":"in collaboration with Gerhard Nagel and Karl Deisseroth,"},{"time":338000,"text":"this vision came to fruition."},{"time":340000,"text":"There's a certain alga that swims in the wild,"},{"time":343000,"text":"and it needs to navigate towards light"},{"time":345000,"text":"in order to photosynthesize optimally."},{"time":347000,"text":"And it senses light with a little eye-spot,"},{"time":349000,"text":"which works not unlike how our eye works."},{"time":352000,"text":"In its membrane, or its boundary,"},{"time":354000,"text":"it contains little proteins"},{"time":357000,"text":"that indeed can convert light into electricity."},{"time":360000,"text":"So these molecules are called channelrhodopsins."},{"time":363000,"text":"And each of these proteins acts just like that solar cell that I told you about."},{"time":366000,"text":"When blue light hits it, it opens up a little hole"},{"time":369000,"text":"and allows charged particles to enter the eye-spot,"},{"time":371000,"text":"and that allows this eye-spot to have an electrical signal"},{"time":373000,"text":"just like a solar cell charging up a battery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":376000,"text":"So what we need to do is to take these molecules"},{"time":378000,"text":"and somehow install them in neurons."},{"time":380000,"text":"And because it's a protein,"},{"time":382000,"text":"it's encoded for in the DNA of this organism."},{"time":385000,"text":"So all we've got to do is take that DNA,"},{"time":387000,"text":"put it into a gene therapy vector, like a virus,"},{"time":390000,"text":"and put it into neurons."},{"time":393000,"text":"So it turned out that this was a very productive time in gene therapy,"},{"time":396000,"text":"and lots of viruses were coming along."},{"time":398000,"text":"So this turned out to be very simple to do."},{"time":400000,"text":"And early in the morning one day in the summer of 2004,"},{"time":403000,"text":"we gave it a try, and it worked on the first try."},{"time":405000,"text":"You take this DNA and you put it into a neuron."},{"time":408000,"text":"The neuron uses its natural protein-making machinery"},{"time":411000,"text":"to fabricate these little light-sensitive proteins"},{"time":413000,"text":"and install them all over the cell,"},{"time":415000,"text":"like putting solar panels on a roof,"},{"time":417000,"text":"and the next thing you know,"},{"time":419000,"text":"you have a neuron which can be activated with light."},{"time":421000,"text":"So this is very powerful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":423000,"text":"One of the tricks you have to do"},{"time":425000,"text":"is to figure out how to deliver these genes to the cells that you want"},{"time":427000,"text":"and not all the other neighbors."},{"time":429000,"text":"And you can do that; you can tweak the viruses"},{"time":431000,"text":"so they hit just some cells and not others."},{"time":433000,"text":"And there's other genetic tricks you can play"},{"time":435000,"text":"in order to get light-activated cells."},{"time":438000,"text":"This field has now come to be known as optogenetics."},{"time":442000,"text":"And just as one example of the kind of thing you can do,"},{"time":444000,"text":"you can take a complex network,"},{"time":446000,"text":"use one of these viruses to deliver the gene"},{"time":448000,"text":"just to one kind of cell in this dense network."},{"time":451000,"text":"And then when you shine light on the entire network,"},{"time":453000,"text":"just that cell type will be activated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455000,"text":"So for example, lets sort of consider that basket cell I told you about earlier --"},{"time":458000,"text":"the one that's atrophied in schizophrenia"},{"time":460000,"text":"and the one that is inhibitory."},{"time":462000,"text":"If we can deliver that gene to these cells --"},{"time":464000,"text":"and they're not going to be altered by the expression of the gene, of course --"},{"time":467000,"text":"and then flash blue light over the entire brain network,"},{"time":470000,"text":"just these cells are going to be driven."},{"time":472000,"text":"And when the light turns off, these cells go back to normal,"},{"time":474000,"text":"so they don't seem to be averse against that."},{"time":477000,"text":"Not only can you use this to study what these cells do,"},{"time":479000,"text":"what their power is in computing in the brain,"},{"time":481000,"text":"but you can also use this to try to figure out --"},{"time":483000,"text":"well maybe we could jazz up the activity of these cells,"},{"time":485000,"text":"if indeed they're atrophied."}]},{"cues":[{"time":487000,"text":"Now I want to tell you a couple of short stories"},{"time":489000,"text":"about how we're using this,"},{"time":491000,"text":"both at the scientific, clinical and pre-clinical levels."},{"time":494000,"text":"One of the questions we've confronted"},{"time":496000,"text":"is, what are the signals in the brain that mediate the sensation of reward?"},{"time":499000,"text":"Because if you could find those,"},{"time":501000,"text":"those would be some of the signals that could drive learning."},{"time":503000,"text":"The brain will do more of whatever got that reward."},{"time":505000,"text":"And also these are signals that go awry in disorders such as addiction."},{"time":508000,"text":"So if we could figure out what cells they are,"},{"time":510000,"text":"we could maybe find new targets"},{"time":512000,"text":"for which drugs could be designed or screened against,"},{"time":514000,"text":"or maybe places where electrodes could be put in"},{"time":516000,"text":"for people who have very severe disability."},{"time":519000,"text":"So to do that, we came up with a very simple paradigm"},{"time":521000,"text":"in collaboration with the Fiorella group,"},{"time":523000,"text":"where one side of this little box,"},{"time":525000,"text":"if the animal goes there, the animal gets a pulse of light"},{"time":527000,"text":"in order to make different cells in the brain sensitive to light."},{"time":529000,"text":"So if these cells can mediate reward,"},{"time":531000,"text":"the animal should go there more and more."},{"time":533000,"text":"And so that's what happens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":535000,"text":"This animal's going to go to the right-hand side and poke his nose there,"},{"time":537000,"text":"and he gets a flash of blue light every time he does that."},{"time":539000,"text":"And he'll do that hundreds and hundreds of times."},{"time":541000,"text":"These are the dopamine neurons,"},{"time":543000,"text":"which some of you may have heard about, in some of the pleasure centers in the brain."},{"time":545000,"text":"Now we've shown that a brief activation of these"},{"time":547000,"text":"is enough, indeed, to drive learning."},{"time":549000,"text":"Now we can generalize the idea."},{"time":551000,"text":"Instead of one point in the brain,"},{"time":553000,"text":"we can devise devices that span the brain,"},{"time":555000,"text":"that can deliver light into three-dimensional patterns --"},{"time":557000,"text":"arrays of optical fibers,"},{"time":559000,"text":"each coupled to its own independent miniature light source."},{"time":561000,"text":"And then we can try to do things in vivo"},{"time":563000,"text":"that have only been done to-date in a dish --"},{"time":566000,"text":"like high-throughput screening throughout the entire brain"},{"time":568000,"text":"for the signals that can cause certain things to happen."},{"time":570000,"text":"Or that could be good clinical targets"},{"time":572000,"text":"for treating brain disorders."}]},{"cues":[{"time":574000,"text":"And one story I want to tell you about"},{"time":576000,"text":"is how can we find targets for treating post-traumatic stress disorder --"},{"time":579000,"text":"a form of uncontrolled anxiety and fear."},{"time":582000,"text":"And one of the things that we did"},{"time":584000,"text":"was to adopt a very classical model of fear."},{"time":587000,"text":"This goes back to the Pavlovian days."},{"time":590000,"text":"It's called Pavlovian fear conditioning --"},{"time":592000,"text":"where a tone ends with a brief shock."},{"time":594000,"text":"The shock isn't painful, but it's a little annoying."},{"time":596000,"text":"And over time -- in this case, a mouse,"},{"time":598000,"text":"which is a good animal model, commonly used in such experiments --"},{"time":600000,"text":"the animal learns to fear the tone."},{"time":602000,"text":"The animal will react by freezing,"},{"time":604000,"text":"sort of like a deer in the headlights."},{"time":606000,"text":"Now the question is, what targets in the brain can we find"},{"time":609000,"text":"that allow us to overcome this fear?"},{"time":611000,"text":"So what we do is we play that tone again"},{"time":613000,"text":"after it's been associated with fear."},{"time":615000,"text":"But we activate targets in the brain, different ones,"},{"time":617000,"text":"using that optical fiber array I told you about in the previous slide,"},{"time":620000,"text":"in order to try and figure out which targets"},{"time":622000,"text":"can cause the brain to overcome that memory of fear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":625000,"text":"And so this brief video"},{"time":627000,"text":"shows you one of these targets that we're working on now."},{"time":629000,"text":"This is an area in the prefrontal cortex,"},{"time":631000,"text":"a region where we can use cognition to try to overcome aversive emotional states."},{"time":634000,"text":"And the animal's going to hear a tone -- and a flash of light occurred there."},{"time":636000,"text":"There's no audio on this, but you can see the animal's freezing."},{"time":638000,"text":"This tone used to mean bad news."},{"time":640000,"text":"And there's a little clock in the lower left-hand corner,"},{"time":642000,"text":"so you can see the animal is about two minutes into this."},{"time":645000,"text":"And now this next clip"},{"time":647000,"text":"is just eight minutes later."},{"time":649000,"text":"And the same tone is going to play, and the light is going to flash again."},{"time":652000,"text":"Okay, there it goes. Right now."},{"time":655000,"text":"And now you can see, just 10 minutes into the experiment,"},{"time":658000,"text":"that we've equipped the brain by photoactivating this area"},{"time":661000,"text":"to overcome the expression"},{"time":663000,"text":"of this fear memory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665000,"text":"Now over the last couple of years, we've gone back to the tree of life"},{"time":668000,"text":"because we wanted to find ways to turn circuits in the brain off."},{"time":671000,"text":"If we could do that, this could be extremely powerful."},{"time":674000,"text":"If you can delete cells just for a few milliseconds or seconds,"},{"time":677000,"text":"you can figure out what necessary role they play"},{"time":679000,"text":"in the circuits in which they're embedded."},{"time":681000,"text":"And we've now surveyed organisms from all over the tree of life --"},{"time":683000,"text":"every kingdom of life except for animals, we see slightly differently."},{"time":686000,"text":"And we found all sorts of molecules, they're called halorhodopsins or archaerhodopsins,"},{"time":689000,"text":"that respond to green and yellow light."},{"time":691000,"text":"And they do the opposite thing of the molecule I told you about before"},{"time":693000,"text":"with the blue light activator channelrhodopsin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":697000,"text":"Let's give an example of where we think this is going to go."},{"time":700000,"text":"Consider, for example, a condition like epilepsy,"},{"time":703000,"text":"where the brain is overactive."},{"time":705000,"text":"Now if drugs fail in epileptic treatment,"},{"time":707000,"text":"one of the strategies is to remove part of the brain."},{"time":709000,"text":"But that's obviously irreversible, and there could be side effects."},{"time":711000,"text":"What if we could just turn off that brain for a brief amount of time,"},{"time":714000,"text":"until the seizure dies away,"},{"time":717000,"text":"and cause the brain to be restored to its initial state --"},{"time":720000,"text":"sort of like a dynamical system that's being coaxed down into a stable state."},{"time":723000,"text":"So this animation just tries to explain this concept"},{"time":726000,"text":"where we made these cells sensitive to being turned off with light,"},{"time":728000,"text":"and we beam light in,"},{"time":730000,"text":"and just for the time it takes to shut down a seizure,"},{"time":732000,"text":"we're hoping to be able to turn it off."},{"time":734000,"text":"And so we don't have data to show you on this front,"},{"time":736000,"text":"but we're very excited about this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":738000,"text":"Now I want to close on one story,"},{"time":740000,"text":"which we think is another possibility --"},{"time":742000,"text":"which is that maybe these molecules, if you can do ultra-precise control,"},{"time":744000,"text":"can be used in the brain itself"},{"time":746000,"text":"to make a new kind of prosthetic, an optical prosthetic."},{"time":749000,"text":"I already told you that electrical stimulators are not uncommon."},{"time":752000,"text":"Seventy-five thousand people have Parkinson's deep-brain stimulators implanted."},{"time":755000,"text":"Maybe 100,000 people have Cochlear implants,"},{"time":757000,"text":"which allow them to hear."},{"time":759000,"text":"There's another thing, which is you've got to get these genes into cells."},{"time":762000,"text":"And new hope in gene therapy has been developed"},{"time":765000,"text":"because viruses like the adeno-associated virus,"},{"time":767000,"text":"which probably most of us around this room have,"},{"time":769000,"text":"and it doesn't have any symptoms,"},{"time":771000,"text":"which have been used in hundreds of patients"},{"time":773000,"text":"to deliver genes into the brain or the body."},{"time":775000,"text":"And so far, there have not been serious adverse events"},{"time":777000,"text":"associated with the virus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":779000,"text":"There's one last elephant in the room, the proteins themselves,"},{"time":782000,"text":"which come from algae and bacteria and fungi,"},{"time":784000,"text":"and all over the tree of life."},{"time":786000,"text":"Most of us don't have fungi or algae in our brains,"},{"time":788000,"text":"so what is our brain going to do if we put that in?"},{"time":790000,"text":"Are the cells going to tolerate it? Will the immune system react?"},{"time":792000,"text":"In its early days -- these have not been done on humans yet --"},{"time":794000,"text":"but we're working on a variety of studies"},{"time":796000,"text":"to try and examine this,"},{"time":798000,"text":"and so far we haven't seen overt reactions of any severity"},{"time":801000,"text":"to these molecules"},{"time":803000,"text":"or to the illumination of the brain with light."},{"time":806000,"text":"So it's early days, to be upfront, but we're excited about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":809000,"text":"I wanted to close with one story,"},{"time":811000,"text":"which we think could potentially"},{"time":813000,"text":"be a clinical application."},{"time":815000,"text":"Now there are many forms of blindness"},{"time":817000,"text":"where the photoreceptors,"},{"time":819000,"text":"our light sensors that are in the back of our eye, are gone."},{"time":822000,"text":"And the retina, of course, is a complex structure."},{"time":824000,"text":"Now let's zoom in on it here, so we can see it in more detail."},{"time":826000,"text":"The photoreceptor cells are shown here at the top,"},{"time":829000,"text":"and then the signals that are detected by the photoreceptors"},{"time":831000,"text":"are transformed by various computations"},{"time":833000,"text":"until finally that layer of cells at the bottom, the ganglion cells,"},{"time":836000,"text":"relay the information to the brain,"},{"time":838000,"text":"where we see that as perception."},{"time":840000,"text":"In many forms of blindness, like retinitis pigmentosa,"},{"time":843000,"text":"or macular degeneration,"},{"time":845000,"text":"the photoreceptor cells have atrophied or been destroyed."},{"time":848000,"text":"Now how could you repair this?"},{"time":850000,"text":"It's not even clear that a drug could cause this to be restored,"},{"time":853000,"text":"because there's nothing for the drug to bind to."},{"time":855000,"text":"On the other hand, light can still get into the eye."},{"time":857000,"text":"The eye is still transparent and you can get light in."},{"time":860000,"text":"So what if we could just take these channelrhodopsins and other molecules"},{"time":863000,"text":"and install them on some of these other spare cells"},{"time":865000,"text":"and convert them into little cameras."},{"time":867000,"text":"And because there's so many of these cells in the eye,"},{"time":869000,"text":"potentially, they could be very high-resolution cameras."}]},{"cues":[{"time":872000,"text":"So this is some work that we're doing."},{"time":874000,"text":"It's being led by one of our collaborators,"},{"time":876000,"text":"Alan Horsager at USC,"},{"time":878000,"text":"and being sought to be commercialized by a start-up company Eos Neuroscience,"},{"time":881000,"text":"which is funded by the NIH."},{"time":883000,"text":"And what you see here is a mouse trying to solve a maze."},{"time":885000,"text":"It's a six-arm maze. And there's a bit of water in the maze"},{"time":887000,"text":"to motivate the mouse to move, or he'll just sit there."},{"time":889000,"text":"And the goal, of course, of this maze"},{"time":891000,"text":"is to get out of the water and go to a little platform"},{"time":893000,"text":"that's under the lit top port."},{"time":895000,"text":"Now mice are smart, so this mouse solves the maze eventually,"},{"time":898000,"text":"but he does a brute-force search."},{"time":900000,"text":"He's swimming down every avenue until he finally gets to the platform."},{"time":903000,"text":"So he's not using vision to do it."},{"time":905000,"text":"These different mice are different mutations"},{"time":907000,"text":"that recapitulate different kinds of blindness that affect humans."},{"time":910000,"text":"And so we're being careful in trying to look at these different models"},{"time":913000,"text":"so we come up with a generalized approach."}]},{"cues":[{"time":915000,"text":"So how are we going to solve this?"},{"time":917000,"text":"We're going to do exactly what we outlined in the previous slide."},{"time":919000,"text":"We're going to take these blue light photosensors"},{"time":921000,"text":"and install them on a layer of cells"},{"time":923000,"text":"in the middle of the retina in the back of the eye"},{"time":926000,"text":"and convert them into a camera --"},{"time":928000,"text":"just like installing solar cells all over those neurons"},{"time":930000,"text":"to make them light sensitive."},{"time":932000,"text":"Light is converted to electricity on them."},{"time":934000,"text":"So this mouse was blind a couple weeks before this experiment"},{"time":937000,"text":"and received one dose of this photosensitive molecule in a virus."},{"time":940000,"text":"And now you can see, the animal can indeed avoid walls"},{"time":942000,"text":"and go to this little platform"},{"time":944000,"text":"and make cognitive use of its eyes again."},{"time":947000,"text":"And to point out the power of this:"},{"time":949000,"text":"these animals are able to get to that platform"},{"time":951000,"text":"just as fast as animals that have seen their entire lives."},{"time":953000,"text":"So this pre-clinical study, I think,"},{"time":955000,"text":"bodes hope for the kinds of things"},{"time":957000,"text":"we're hoping to do in the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":959000,"text":"To close, I want to point out that we're also exploring"},{"time":962000,"text":"new business models for this new field of neurotechnology."},{"time":964000,"text":"We're developing these tools,"},{"time":966000,"text":"but we share them freely with hundreds of groups all over the world,"},{"time":968000,"text":"so people can study and try to treat different disorders."},{"time":970000,"text":"And our hope is that, by figuring out brain circuits"},{"time":973000,"text":"at a level of abstraction that lets us repair them and engineer them,"},{"time":976000,"text":"we can take some of these intractable disorders that I told you about earlier,"},{"time":979000,"text":"practically none of which are cured,"},{"time":981000,"text":"and in the 21st century make them history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":983000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":985000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":998000,"text":"Juan Enriquez: So some of the stuff is a little dense."},{"time":1001000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1003000,"text":"But the implications"},{"time":1005000,"text":"of being able to control seizures or epilepsy"},{"time":1008000,"text":"with light instead of drugs,"},{"time":1010000,"text":"and being able to target those specifically"},{"time":1013000,"text":"is a first step."},{"time":1015000,"text":"The second thing that I think I heard you say"},{"time":1017000,"text":"is you can now control the brain in two colors,"},{"time":1020000,"text":"like an on/off switch."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1022000,"text":"Ed Boyden: That's right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1024000,"text":"JE: Which makes every impulse going through the brain a binary code."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1027000,"text":"EB: Right, yeah."},{"time":1029000,"text":"So with blue light, we can drive information, and it's in the form of a one."},{"time":1032000,"text":"And by turning things off, it's more or less a zero."},{"time":1034000,"text":"So our hope is to eventually build brain coprocessors"},{"time":1036000,"text":"that work with the brain"},{"time":1038000,"text":"so we can augment functions in people with disabilities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1041000,"text":"JE: And in theory, that means that,"},{"time":1043000,"text":"as a mouse feels, smells,"},{"time":1045000,"text":"hears, touches,"},{"time":1047000,"text":"you can model it out as a string of ones and zeros."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1050000,"text":"EB: Sure, yeah. We're hoping to use this as a way of testing"},{"time":1052000,"text":"what neural codes can drive certain behaviors"},{"time":1054000,"text":"and certain thoughts and certain feelings,"},{"time":1056000,"text":"and use that to understand more about the brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1059000,"text":"JE: Does that mean that some day you could download memories"},{"time":1062000,"text":"and maybe upload them?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1064000,"text":"EB: Well that's something we're starting to work on very hard."},{"time":1066000,"text":"We're now working on some work"},{"time":1068000,"text":"where we're trying to tile the brain with recording elements too."},{"time":1070000,"text":"So we can record information and then drive information back in --"},{"time":1073000,"text":"sort of computing what the brain needs"},{"time":1075000,"text":"in order to augment its information processing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1077000,"text":"JE: Well, that might change a couple things. Thank you. (EB: Thank you.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1080000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}